I think all three brands are in the right healthwellnessathleisure space and here to stay But equity wise given I believe in all three brands I think UA is the most attractive

if it had the same 108 net margin as NKE in its most recent qtr its ttm EPS would be around 120 At 40 that would imply a PE of 336 lower than NKEs and substantially lower than LULUs Thats based on ttm and presumably UA wouldnt get that multiple for flat sales

I think it can easily return to respectable sales growth and its already in the process of shifting its sales mix to lift margins Athleisure  wellness focus and thus all 3 brands are here to stay Question is valuation If UA traded at 4x revs the stock would be 40 and

in prior quarters its net margins were more like NKEs So then its a question of sales growth Is 1520 sales growth sustainable given LULU is now much larger Certainly if LULU maintains its margins and sales growth it will go much higher Id rather bet on UA because

1 Stagnant sales growth 2 Shitty profit marginsNonetheless NKE grows revenue in the respectable single digits That should be attainable for UA And UA is making progress in shifting its sales mix to lift margins LULU is a good buy if it can keep the 20 margin but

Definitely think LULU is a great brand that executes well but 9x ttm revenue UA has had shitty execution over the last few years but trading under 1x revenue NKE trades at 4x on much higher revs Why is UA trading at such a dramatically different multiple Two reasons
